---
import SiteShell from './_components/SiteShell.astro';
---
<SiteShell title="Article — ScoreTap" activePage="news">

  <style>
    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

    .article-container {
      max-width: 1280px;
      margin: 16px auto;
      padding: 0 16px;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 320px;
      gap: 16px;
    }
    .article-main { min-width: 0; }
    .article-sidebar { min-width: 0; }

    .breadcrumb { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-dim); padding: 8px 0 12px; }
    .breadcrumb a { color: var(--accent); }
    .breadcrumb a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    .article-card {
      background: var(--bg-panel);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-top: 3px solid var(--accent);
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .article-header {
      padding: 24px 28px 20px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .article-meta-top {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      font-size: 10px;
    }
    .article-title {
      font-size: 1.6rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      color: var(--text-bright);
      line-height: 1.25;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .article-byline {
      font-size: 11px;
      color: var(--text-dim);
      display: flex;
      gap: 12px;
      align-items: center;
    }
    .article-byline .author { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 700; }

    /* ── BODY TYPOGRAPHY ── */
    .article-body { padding: 28px 28px 32px; }

    .article-body h2 {
      font-size: 18px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text-bright);
      margin: 36px 0 16px;
      padding-bottom: 7px;
      border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
    }
    .article-body h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }

    .article-body h3 {
      font-size: 15px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text-bright);
      margin: 28px 0 12px;
      padding-bottom: 5px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    .article-body h4 {
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--accent);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 1.5px;
      margin: 20px 0 8px;
    }

    .article-body p {
      font-size: 14px;
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1.75;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
    }
    .article-body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

    .article-body strong {
      color: var(--text-bright);
      font-weight: 700;
    }
    .article-body em {
      font-style: italic;
      color: #b0b0c0;
    }
    .article-body a {
      color: var(--accent);
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-decoration-color: #ff6b0040;
    }
    .article-body a:hover {
      text-decoration-color: var(--accent);
    }

    .pull-quote {
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0e0e18, #111122);
      padding: 20px 24px;
      margin: 24px 0;
      font-size: 14px;
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--text-bright);
      line-height: 1.7;
    }
    .pull-quote cite {
      display: block;
      font-style: normal;
      font-size: 11px;
      color: var(--accent);
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-top: 8px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    }

    .stats-box {
      background: var(--bg-panel);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      margin: 24px 0;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .stats-box-title {
      font-size: 12px;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 1.5px;
      color: var(--accent);
      padding: 10px 14px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1e1e30, #181828);
      border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
    }
    .stats-row {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 7px 14px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      font-size: 12px;
    }
    .stats-box-body .stats-row:nth-child(odd) { background: var(--bg-panel); }
    .stats-box-body .stats-row:nth-child(even) { background: var(--bg-row-alt); }
    .stats-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .stats-label { color: var(--text-dim); }
    .stats-value { color: var(--text-bright); font-weight: 700; font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; letter-spacing: 0.5px; }

    /* ── TABLE OF CONTENTS ── */
    .article-toc {
      display: inline-block;
      background: var(--bg-panel);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      min-width: 260px;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }
    .article-toc-title {
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text-bright);
      padding: 10px 14px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1e1e30, #181828);
      border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
      cursor: pointer;
      user-select: none;
    }
    .article-toc-title::after {
      content: ' [hide]';
      font-size: 10px;
      color: var(--accent);
      font-weight: 400;
    }
    .article-toc-title.collapsed::after {
      content: ' [show]';
    }
    .article-toc-list {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 10px 14px;
      margin: 0;
      counter-reset: toc-counter;
    }
    .article-toc-list li {
      counter-increment: toc-counter;
      padding: 4px 0;
      font-size: 13px;
    }
    .article-toc-list li::before {
      content: counter(toc-counter) ". ";
      color: var(--accent);
      font-weight: 700;
    }
    .article-toc-list a {
      color: var(--text);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    .article-toc-list a:hover {
      color: var(--accent);
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    /* ── WIKI-STYLE TABLES ── */
    .article-body table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin: 24px 0;
      font-size: 12px;
    }
    .article-body th {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1e1e30, #181828);
      color: var(--text-bright);
      font-weight: 700;
      text-align: left;
      padding: 8px 12px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .article-body td {
      padding: 7px 12px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      color: var(--text);
    }
    .article-body tr:nth-child(odd) td { background: var(--bg-panel); }
    .article-body tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--bg-row-alt); }
    .article-body tr:hover td { background: #1a1a2e; }

    .related-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .related-card {
      padding: 14px;
      border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .related-card:last-child { border-right: none; }
    .related-card:hover { background: #131320; }
    .related-headline {
      font-size: 12px;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--text-bright);
      line-height: 1.5;
      margin-bottom: 6px;
      display: block;
    }
    .related-headline:hover { color: var(--accent); }
    .related-meta { font-size: 10px; color: var(--text-dim); display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center; }

    .sidebar-news-list { list-style: none; }
    .sidebar-news-list li {
      padding: 8px 10px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      font-size: 11px;
    }
    .sidebar-news-list li:nth-child(odd)  { background: var(--bg-panel); }
    .sidebar-news-list li:nth-child(even) { background: var(--bg-row-alt); }
    .sidebar-news-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .sidebar-news-list a { color: var(--text); line-height: 1.4; display: block; }
    .sidebar-news-list a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
    .sidebar-news-meta { font-size: 10px; color: var(--text-dim); margin-top: 2px; }

    #article-not-found {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 40px;
      color: var(--text-dim);
      font-size: 1rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      background: var(--bg-panel);
    }
  </style>

  <div class="article-container">
    <div class="article-main">
      <div class="breadcrumb" id="article-breadcrumb">
        <a href="/l1/scoretap/">Home</a> &rsaquo;
        <a href="/l1/scoretap/news">News</a> &rsaquo;
        <span id="breadcrumb-title">Loading&hellip;</span>
      </div>
      <div id="article-content"></div>
      <div id="article-not-found" style="display:none;">
        Article not found. <a href="/l1/scoretap/news" style="color:var(--accent);">Return to News</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="article-sidebar">
      <div class="widget" style="margin-bottom:10px;">
        <div class="widget-header">
          <span class="widget-title">Latest News</span>
          <a class="widget-link" href="/l1/scoretap/news">All News</a>
        </div>
        <ul class="sidebar-news-list" id="sidebar-news-list"></ul>
      </div>
      <div class="widget">
        <div class="widget-header">
          <span class="widget-title">Top Events</span>
          <a class="widget-link" href="#">All Events</a>
        </div>
        <div class="event-row"><div class="event-name">IEM Katowice 2026</div><div style="text-align:right;"><span class="game-tag cs2">CS2</span><div class="event-dates">Mar 5&ndash;15</div></div><span class="event-badge live">LIVE</span></div>
        <div class="event-row"><div class="event-name">VCT Americas 2026</div><div style="text-align:right;"><span class="game-tag valorant">VAL</span><div class="event-dates">Mar 1&ndash;20</div></div><span class="event-badge live">LIVE</span></div>
        <div class="event-row"><div class="event-name">RLCS 2026 Spring</div><div style="text-align:right;"><span class="game-tag rl">RL</span><div class="event-dates">Mar 8&ndash;22</div></div><span class="event-badge live">LIVE</span></div>
        <div class="event-row"><div class="event-name">LCK Spring 2026</div><div style="text-align:right;"><span class="game-tag lol">LOL</span><div class="event-dates">Feb 15&ndash;Apr 5</div></div><span class="event-badge live">LIVE</span></div>
        <div class="event-row"><div class="event-name">ESL One Stockholm 2026</div><div style="text-align:right;"><span class="game-tag dota2">DOTA</span><div class="event-dates">Mar 20&ndash;30</div></div><span class="event-badge upcoming">UPCOMING</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
  // ── HELPERS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  function pq(text, cite) {
    return '<blockquote class="pull-quote">&ldquo;' + text + '&rdquo;<cite>&mdash; ' + cite + '</cite></blockquote>';
  }

  function sb(title, rows) {
    var html = '<div class="stats-box"><div class="stats-box-title">' + title + '</div><div class="stats-box-body">';
    rows.forEach(function(r) {
      html += '<div class="stats-row"><span class="stats-label">' + r[0] + '</span><span class="stats-value">' + r[1] + '</span></div>';
    });
    return html + '</div></div>';
  }

  function a(href, text) { return '<a href="' + href + '">' + text + '</a>'; }
  function art(id, text) { return a('/l1/scoretap/article?id=' + id, text); }
  function teams(text) { return a('/l1/scoretap/teams', text); }

  // ── ARTICLES ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  var ARTICLES = {

    'zywoo-katowice-record': {
      id: 'zywoo-katowice-record',
      game: 'cs2', gameLabel: 'CS2',
      title: 'ZywOo Sets New Career-High Rating Record at IEM Katowice 2026',
      author: 'Marcus Holt', date: 'Mar 11, 2026 · 2h ago', event: 'IEM Katowice 2026',
      related: ['navi-blamef-signing', 'mouz-heroic-semifinal', 'vitality-faze-results'],
      body: [
        '<h2>A Performance for the Ages</h2>',
        '<p><strong>Mathieu &ldquo;ZywOo&rdquo; Herbaut</strong> has delivered the most dominant individual performance in recent CS2 history, posting a <strong>1.42 HLTV rating</strong> across eight maps at <em>IEM Katowice 2026</em>, the highest recorded by any player at a Major-tier event since the transition from CS:GO. ' + teams('Team Vitality') + ' advance to the semifinals on the back of a display that left analysts reaching for superlatives they had already exhausted.</p>',
        '<p>The French superstar was particularly lethal on <strong>Mirage</strong> and <strong>Inferno</strong>, where he averaged over <strong>92 ADR</strong> and closed out rounds in moments that would have otherwise slipped from Vitality\'s grasp. His <strong>opening-duel win rate of 67%</strong> forced entire opposing strategies to bend around the question of how to avoid him, which inevitably meant gifting space elsewhere.</p>',
        pq('I never think about ratings. I just try to make the right call every round. If the numbers are high, it means the team is in good shape.', 'ZywOo, post-match press conference'),
        '<h2>The Group Stage in Detail</h2>',
        '<p>ZywOo\'s brilliance carried Vitality through a brutal group that included <strong>G2 Esports</strong> and <strong>MOUZ</strong>. Against G2, in what many considered a potential final preview, he dropped <strong>32 kills</strong> on the deciding map while holding a <strong>1.58 series rating</strong>. ' + art('g2-niko-interview', 'NiKo later said') + ' they had prepared specifically for ZywOo but that &ldquo;he found ways we hadn\'t anticipated.&rdquo;</p>',
        sb('IEM Katowice 2026 — ZywOo Stats', [
          ['HLTV Rating (8 maps)', '1.42'],
          ['K/D Ratio', '1.61'],
          ['ADR (Average Damage/Round)', '88.4'],
          ['Headshot %', '52.3%'],
          ['Opening Kill Win %', '67%'],
          ['Clutch Rounds Won', '7'],
        ]),
        '<h2>What Comes Next</h2>',
        '<p>With Vitality in the semifinals, ZywOo now faces ' + teams('NAVI') + ' and the recently signed ' + art('navi-blamef-signing', '<strong>blameF</strong>') + ', who has brought a physical, map-controlling rifle game that Head Coach <strong>B1ad3</strong> says he has been building toward for years. Whether ZywOo\'s historic form continues against that style of late-round defense will define whether Vitality lift the trophy on Sunday.</p>',
        '<p><em>Vitality\'s semifinal kicks off Thursday at 17:00 CET. Follow live scores on ' + a('/l1/scoretap/', 'ScoreTap\'s scores page') + '.</em></p>',
      ],
    },

    'navi-blamef-signing': {
      id: 'navi-blamef-signing',
      game: 'cs2', gameLabel: 'CS2',
      title: 'NAVI Confirm Signing of Rifler blameF Ahead of Major Qualifier',
      author: 'Elena Vasquez', date: 'Mar 11, 2026 · 4h ago', event: 'Transfer News',
      related: ['zywoo-katowice-record', 'cs2-major-copenhagen', 'vitality-faze-results'],
      body: [
        '<h2>The Signing</h2>',
        '<p><strong>Natus Vincere</strong> have officially confirmed the acquisition of Danish rifler <strong>Kristian &ldquo;blameF&rdquo; Steffensen</strong>, ending weeks of speculation following his departure from <em>Astralis</em>. The 26-year-old joins a rebuilt NAVI core alongside emerging Ukrainian fragger <strong>iM</strong> and veteran <strong>electronic</strong>, giving Head Coach <strong>B1ad3</strong> the physical rifle presence he has publicly sought since early 2025.</p>',
        '<p>blameF arrives with a reputation as one of the most imposing individual riflers in the world. His win rate in duels from <em>unexpected</em> positions consistently outperforms the statistical expectation for any given angle. His <strong>2025 ESL Pro League</strong> run averaged a <strong>1.24 rating across 14 maps</strong>, with a first-kill percentage that ranked <strong>fourth globally</strong>.</p>',
        pq('NAVI is the club I dreamed about playing for when I was sixteen years old. This signing is not just a career move. It is a chapter I have been building toward.', 'blameF, signing announcement'),
        '<h2>Why NAVI Needed This</h2>',
        '<p>The signing is a direct response to NAVI\'s inability to close out matches in 2025, a period in which the team repeatedly traded fraggers inefficiently in late-round situations. ' + teams('NAVI') + '\'s <strong>late-round win rate in 2025 ranked ninth among top-16 teams</strong>, a damning number for a squad with individual talent of that calibre. blameF\'s high opening-kill percentage addresses the structural deficit that B1ad3\'s system had been unable to paper over.</p>',
        sb('blameF — Career Snapshot', [
          ['Previous Team', 'Astralis'],
          ['2025 HLTV Rating', '1.18'],
          ['Career Majors', '3'],
          ['First-Kill % (2025)', '64.2%'],
          ['Contract Length', '2 years'],
        ]),
        '<h2>The Road to the Major Qualifier</h2>',
        '<p>NAVI enter the upcoming Major qualifier ranked <strong>#2 in the world</strong>, sitting directly behind ' + art('zywoo-katowice-record', 'Vitality') + ' in the standings. The qualifier begins just three days after <em>IEM Katowice</em> concludes, giving blameF minimal integration time before elimination pressure arrives. B1ad3 is unbothered: <em>&ldquo;Pressure reveals what players are made of. We already know what blameF is made of.&rdquo;</em></p>',
        '<p>The ' + art('cs2-major-copenhagen', 'CS2 Major 2026 in Copenhagen') + ' is the explicit target for this new-look lineup. Securing attendance would give blameF his fourth Major appearance and NAVI their first Major title shot since 2023.</p>',
      ],
    },

    'cs2-major-copenhagen': {
      id: 'cs2-major-copenhagen',
      game: 'cs2', gameLabel: 'CS2',
      title: 'CS2 Major 2026 Location Officially Announced — Copenhagen Confirmed',
      author: 'James Archer', date: 'Mar 11, 2026 · 6h ago', event: 'CS2 Major 2026',
      related: ['navi-blamef-signing', 'blast-premier-schedule', 'zywoo-katowice-record'],
      body: [
        '<h2>Royal Arena Returns</h2>',
        '<p><strong>Valve</strong> and <strong>PGL</strong> have jointly confirmed that the <em>CS2 Major 2026</em> will take place in <strong>Copenhagen, Denmark</strong> at the <strong>Royal Arena</strong>, a 16,000-capacity venue that last hosted a CS:GO Major in 2022 and is widely regarded as one of the finest esports venues in Europe for its atmosphere, acoustics, and crowd proximity to the stage. The event runs <strong>June 14&ndash;28</strong> with a record <strong>$1,250,000 prize pool</strong>.</p>',
        pq('Copenhagen has one of the world\'s most passionate CS fan bases. Bringing the Major back here felt inevitable. We cannot wait to fill Royal Arena again.', 'PGL CEO, official press release'),
        '<h2>Format and Structure</h2>',
        '<p>The Major will unfold across three phases: the <strong>Challengers Stage</strong> (24 teams, Swiss format), the <strong>Legends Stage</strong> (16 teams), and the <strong>Champions Stage</strong> (8 teams, single-elimination bracket). Teams currently ranked inside the <strong>top 10 of the Valve ranking</strong> are expected to receive direct invitations to the Legends Stage, bypassing the Challengers qualifier.</p>',
        sb('CS2 Major 2026 — Key Details', [
          ['Venue', 'Royal Arena, Copenhagen'],
          ['Capacity', '16,000'],
          ['Prize Pool', '$1,250,000'],
          ['Dates', 'June 14–28, 2026'],
          ['Organizer', 'PGL'],
          ['Teams (total)', '24'],
        ]),
        '<h2>Competition and Road to Qualification</h2>',
        '<p>Copenhagen\'s selection beat out competing bids from <strong>Seoul</strong>, <strong>Warsaw</strong>, and <strong>Montreal</strong>. Denmark\'s domestic CS2 scene, home to <strong>blameF</strong>, <strong>Magisk</strong>, and <strong>dupreeh</strong>, ensures local turnout will be exceptional. ' + art('navi-blamef-signing', 'NAVI\'s newly signed blameF') + ' will be one of the most-watched players on home soil if NAVI qualify.</p>',
        '<p>Qualifier pathways will be announced by PGL in the coming weeks. Regional leagues across <em>Europe</em>, <em>Asia</em>, <em>North America</em>, <em>South America</em>, and <em>Oceania</em> will each receive allocation slots. The ' + art('blast-premier-schedule', 'BLAST Premier Spring') + ' is expected to serve as one of the primary European qualifying routes.</p>',
      ],
    },

    'g2-niko-interview': {
      id: 'g2-niko-interview',
      game: 'cs2', gameLabel: 'CS2',
      title: 'G2 NiKo: "We Came to Katowice to Win Everything, Not Just Qualify"',
      author: 'Sophie Lindberg', date: 'Mar 11, 2026 · 16h ago', event: 'IEM Katowice 2026',
      related: ['zywoo-katowice-record', 'mouz-heroic-semifinal', 'vitality-faze-results'],
      body: [
        '<h2>On the Record</h2>',
        '<p>In an extended sit-down following <strong>G2 Esports\'</strong> quarterfinal win, <strong>Nikola &ldquo;NiKo&rdquo; Kovač</strong> was uncharacteristically candid about the pressure, the ambition, and the narrative that has followed him for most of his career. <em>&ldquo;People say we always fall short in the big moments,&rdquo;</em> he said, leaning forward. <em>&ldquo;And yes, there have been times when that has been true. But this version of G2 is different. The depth of our roster is different. I feel that every single round.&rdquo;</em></p>',
        '<p>NiKo has been exceptional at <em>IEM Katowice 2026</em>, posting a <strong>1.31 rating</strong> with <strong>five clutch rounds</strong>, all of which came in rounds where the map was directly at stake. His <strong>1v2 clutch on Nuke in overtime</strong> against Heroic in the quarterfinals was the defining moment of G2\'s run and immediately became one of the most-clipped plays of the event.</p>',
        pq('We came to Katowice to win everything, not just qualify. If we lose now, it means we failed. I do not plan on failing.', 'NiKo, post-match press conference'),
        '<h2>The System Behind the Superstar</h2>',
        '<p>G2\'s Head Coach <strong>Damien &ldquo;maLeK&rdquo; Marcel</strong> has built a system around NiKo\'s game-reading as a <em>secondary decision-maker</em>, not merely a fragger. <em>&ldquo;Nikola understands the game at an architectural level,&rdquo;</em> maLeK explained. <em>&ldquo;He influences mid-round calls from the rifle position in ways that are impossible to counter-stratify because they\'re not predictable.&rdquo;</em></p>',
        sb('NiKo — IEM Katowice 2026 Stats', [
          ['HLTV Rating', '1.31'],
          ['Clutch Rounds Won', '5'],
          ['Opening Kill %', '61%'],
          ['G2 Group Record', '3–1'],
          ['Maps Played', '9'],
        ]),
        '<h2>On the Semifinal vs. Vitality</h2>',
        '<p>The upcoming semifinal against ' + art('zywoo-katowice-record', 'Vitality and ZywOo') + ' is being billed as the de facto Grand Final given the bracket weight. NiKo is direct when pressed: <em>&ldquo;He is the best player in the world right now and I respect him deeply. But we are prepared for him specifically. I will not say more than that.&rdquo;</em></p>',
        '<p><strong>G2 vs. Vitality</strong> kicks off Thursday. ' + a('/l1/scoretap/', 'Watch live on ScoreTap.') + '</p>',
      ],
    },

    'mouz-heroic-semifinal': {
      id: 'mouz-heroic-semifinal',
      game: 'cs2', gameLabel: 'CS2',
      title: 'MOUZ Advance to IEM Katowice Semifinals After 2-0 Sweep of Heroic',
      author: 'Marcus Holt', date: 'Mar 10, 2026 · 18h ago', event: 'IEM Katowice 2026',
      related: ['zywoo-katowice-record', 'g2-niko-interview', 'vitality-faze-results'],
      body: [
        '<h2>Clinical Execution</h2>',
        '<p><strong>MOUZ</strong> produced a near-flawless <strong>2-0 dismantling of Heroic</strong> to book their semifinal spot at <em>IEM Katowice 2026</em>, with Hungarian AWPer <strong>Mátyás &ldquo;torzsi&rdquo; Törzs</strong> leading the charge at an event-best <strong>1.44 rating</strong> across both maps. The result ended Heroic\'s four-map win streak on Inferno and confirmed ' + teams('MOUZ') + ' as the tournament\'s most complete team outside the top seeds.</p>',
